news.title: TARC reports Rs 1,165 crore pre-sale during Q3 FY25
news.para: Customer collections in Q3 FY2025 reached to Rs 181 crore, bringing the total collections for the first three quarters of the fiscal year to Rs 371 crore.

news.title: Sunac China gains backing to restructure one more onshore bond: Source
news.para: Sunac is the first among Chinese developers to attempt to reduce its onshore bond debt through a company-led debt restructuring

news.title: Arkade Developers to redevelop three housing projects in Mumbai
news.para: The company will be developing 20,232 sq meters (approximately five acres) across these redevelopment projects located in Andheri East, Malad West and Borivali West.

news.title: Environmentalists urge Maharashtra CM to stop stone quarrying in Bhayandarpada skyscrapers
news.para: The buildings could cave in due to landslides which are imminent due to the constant quarrying in the area, Watchdog Foundation director advocate Godfrey Pimenta said.

news.title: Real estate boom raise concerns over ecological damage in Dehradun
news.para: They allege that while heavy construction takes place on private land, builders are also encroaching on public land, endangering public safety.

news.title: Rajasthan government revises mining policy for manufactured sand
news.para: Chief Minister and mines minister Bhajan Lal Sharma announced the implementation of a new mineral policy following the formation of the new govt.

news.title: Goa: GCZMA imposes Rs 77.9 lakh fine for CRZ violation in Arambol
news.para: The violation came to light after a local approached the high court in 2023, alleging inaction by various local authorities against the CRZ violation.

news.title: Hong Kong's Logan Group proposes restructuring its $8 billion offshore debt
news.para: Logan Group seeks to restructure $7.56 billion of the total offshore debt, while also aiming to relieve creditors of its additional $476 million offshore debt under separate financing instruments.

news.title: HYDRAA razes illegal five-storey building in Ayyappa Society
news.para: HYDRAA commissioner AV Ranganath, who oversaw the operation, said, "This structure was a glaring example of violations at multiple levels, posing serious risks to public safety and environmental health."

news.title: Chandigarh civic body seeks private entities to maintain its properties
news.para: Besides, the MC is also going to give the work to construct a new community centre in Sector 51 and also to make proper use of the 280-kilometre-long constructed underground duct in the city to lay down multiple service lines to private bidders.

news.title: Property owners of Gunthewari seek tax revision amid concession concerns
news.para: Awachar also said that Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar Municipal Corporation (CSMC) was misleading people by saying that a 50% concession is offered towards regularisation charges

news.title: Goa: New strict guidelines for sand mining in Zuari estuary and Mandovi river
news.para: These guidelines are an integral part of the survey report on sand mining prepared by the South Goa district administration.

news.title: Noida authority seeks state government's help for defaulting industrial and IT plot cases
news.para: The move will give one final chance to the defaulting plot owners to clear their dues and obtain functional certificates.

news.title: BKC to Worli metro will start in 100 days: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Shinde made the announcement after a review meeting of the MMRDA, UD, and Housing departments by CM Devendra Fadnavis. CM Fadnavis instructed officials to make a fresh schedule for the completion of all metro works in the MMRDA area.

news.title: Centre revokes GRAP 3 curbs as air pollution levels dip in Delhi-NCR
news.para: The city's 24-hour average air quality index (AQI) stood at 339 at 4 pm on Sunday.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA recovered Rs 674 crore from defaulting builders in 17 months
news.para: According to UP Rera, a total of 12,472 recovery certificates (RCs) worth Rs 3,778.69 crore have been issued, predominantly in the national capital region.

news.title: Gurugram: DTPE to seal 150 illegally constructed flats in Palam Vihar
news.para: DTPE Amit Madholia has sought police deployment and the appointment of a duty magistrate to oversee the sealing operation.

news.title: Jammu development body cautions public to seek CLU, LPA of plots
news.para: ​​​The government has taken serious note of the massive illegal constructions and the proliferation of unauthorized colonies by various colonizers, attributed to the failure of enforcement wings to curb such activities.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body works to reclaim lake lands
news.para: According to BBMP, private parties have encroached upon 120 lakes, with partial structures present on 88 of them, religious buildings on 42, and slums on 9 lakes.
